@wibblywobblyidiotvision 
If you stick to the strictest definition of "free energy" by mainstream science,  then the term is basically an impossibility, and this tends to imprison our minds into a box.   However,  if you interpret it in terms of "practicality"  then free energy is not only possible,  it's real.   For example,  Our sun has been providing energy for billions and billions of years.   No human civilization could possibly live that long, so by our viewpoint,  it's PRACTICALLY infinite and free.  It's all about perspective.

 Based on my experience with this topic,   "Free energy"  devices are essentially the same as solar panels.  They are just  different forms of energy harvesters or converters.  Unfortunately,  when people hear the words "free energy",  their minds automatically shut down and won't entertain other possibilities.
